An Ikeja Lagos Magistrate’s Court yesterday ordered the remand of two men Jamiu Alao, 21, and Mukaila Jamiu, 23, over attempted murder. The Magistrate, Mrs O.A. Odubajo, who did not take the defendants’ plea, ordered that they should be remanded in Kirikiri Correctional Centre. She, however, directed the police to send the case file to the state Director of Public Prosecutions (DPPs) for legal advice. Odubajo adjourned the case until February 16 for the receipt of the DPP’s advice. The defendants, Alao, a driver, and Jamiu, a mechanic, are being tried for conspiracy, robbery and attempted murder. - Advertisement - The Prosecution Counsel, Sergeant Olasunkanmi Adejumola, told the court that the defendants committed the offences in November 2021 at Ijora Lagos State.   Ekiti asks workers to prepare to work virtually     Gunmen abduct three Chinese workers in Niger     RRS nabs ex-convicts, others for stealing from accident…   He said the defendants robbed one Miss Favour Emmanuel of her bag containing two phones valued at N50,000. Adejumola said the duo attempted to kill the complainant by pushing her out of their tricycle. “The complainant boarded the defendants’ tricycle. While on transit, they robbed her of her bag containing two phones and pushed her out of their moving tricycle. “Some motorists pursued the tricycle and apprehended the defendants,” the prosecutor told the court. According to the prosecutor, the offences violate Sections 297(1) and 230 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. Section 297(1) prescribes 21 years’ jail term for robbery while Section 230 attracts life imprisonment for attempted murder.